BEGIN_PGML
Write a simplified expression for the perimeter of the given shape (which is not drawn to scale).

>> [@image(insertGraph($image_1), width=>564, alt=>qq"a quadrilateral whose sides are labeled $terms[0], $terms[1], $terms[2], and $terms[3].")@]*  <<

[_]{$ans}{20}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The perimeter is the result from adding the six sides together: [`[$termsTeX[0]] + [$termsTeX[1]] + [$termsTeX[2]] + [$termsTeX[3]] + [$termsTeX[4]] + [$termsTeX[5]]\text{.}`] There are two [`[$orig_vars[0]]`]-terms, two [`[$orig_vars[1]]`]-terms, and two [`[$orig_vars[2]]`]-terms. We combine each pair of like terms and the perimeter is [`[$ans]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

